        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria — uncertainty characterization",
        "description": "All model inputs with non-negligible uncertainty must be identified and their probability distributions characterized (type, mean, standard deviation or bounds). At minimum: fluid viscosity, hematocrit, inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and hemolysis model constants. Distributions must be grounded in measurement data or published literature."
